<H5>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="14"> A. Overview</s>
</H5>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="15"> Japanese society and its economy continue to undergo remarkable changes: diversification and sophistication in the people's lifestyle and consciousness, changes in regional and industrial structures, a society made up of increasingly more elderly people, and globalization.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="16"> In addition, there are calls for worldwide cooperation in tackling global environmental problems as an issue common to all of humanity.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="17"> Towards the goal of coping with these socio-economic changes and improving the standard of living, technological development in the field of transportation plays an increasingly important role.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="18"> During FY93 the Ministry of Transport (MOT) will develop railway technology, automotive technology, shipbuilding technology, ocean-utilization technology, space-development technology, and so forth, and will promote the development of technology that covers many fields: improving traffic and transportation safety, improving port and harbor construction technology, mitigating natural disasters, improving disaster-prevention technology, preventing pollution, preserving the environment, etc.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="19"> Table 1 summarizes the MOT-related Special Coordination Funds for Promoting S\|[amp ]\|T in the FY93 budget.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="20"> The subtotal of major expenses for research institutes that are under the MOT's control increased 3.3\|[percnt]\|.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="21"> As for administrative department expenses, transport technology R\|[amp ]\|D expenses increased 3.6\|[percnt]\|, and geostationary meteorological satellite operation expenses increased 19.9\|[percnt]\|, resulting in a 19.1\|[percnt]\| increase in the subtotal.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="22"> The overall expenses under MOT jurisdiction increased 9.8\|[percnt]\|, indicating growth that corresponds to the importance of R\|[amp ]\|D in the field of transportation.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-59756" num="23"> In addition to those expenses, \|[yen ]\|5.767 billion as subsidies for the development of railway technology, such as superconductive magnetic levitation train technology, and \|[yen ]\|996 million as subsidies for advanced ship technology R\|[amp ]\|D are appropriated in the general account.</s>

